Welcome to the PowerFlex All-in-One Monitoring VM (v4.8)

This VM contains a simple solution for monitoring a PowerFlex
Gen1 cluster. InfluxDB, Telegraf, and Grafana are preinstalled and
ready for final configuration. After logging in, you will need to 
run the "prep_monitoring" script in the root directory. Supply IP an
IP address for the VM and also thePowerFlex REST Gateway or Ingress 
IP and credentials. When setup completes, go to the Grafana interface
at https://[ip-of-vm] and login with the default credentials,
which are: admin/powerflex. Sample Grafana templates are supplied
in /var/local/telegraf-powerflex/grafana-dashboards-inxluxdb/
and they are pre-loaded into this VM.

The primary network interface starts with DHCP by default.
Log in via the vCenter or other VM console and run the
setup script to assign a static IP and configure monitoring.

